    <h1>URGENT: Massive Cyber Attack Compromises All U.S. Data</h1>
</header>

<div class="container">
    <div class="alert-box">
        <p><strong>Breaking News:</strong> A hacker known as "Spectre" has compromised sensitive data of millions of Americans, including the Presidentâ€™s classified information. Immediate action is required to safeguard personal data.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="featured-image">
        <img src="WhatsApp Image 2024-11-14 at 10.33.16 AM.jpeg" alt="Digital figure accessing data in front of a government building">
    </div>

    <h2>The Most Unprecedented Cybersecurity Breach in U.S. History</h2>
    <p>In a meticulously planned attack, the hacker known as "Spectre" accessed the most sensitive U.S. government databases. This breach includes personal, financial, and even classified information on American citizens and government officials, including the President of the United States.</p>

    <h2>Details of the Breach</h2>
    <p>Initial investigations reveal Spectre used advanced techniques including zero-day exploits, sophisticated phishing attacks, and malware designed to evade detection. The data compromised includes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Financial records and banking details of U.S. citizens</li>
        <li>Health and biometric data</li>
        <li>Classified government communications</li>
        <li>Confidential information related to national security</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Immediate Steps for All Citizens to Protect Themselves</h2>
    <div class="emergency-steps">
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Change passwords</strong> on all sensitive accounts immediately, using complex and unique passwords for each.</li>
            <li><strong>Enable two-factor authentication (2FA)</strong> on all accounts for an additional layer of security.</li>
            <li><strong>Monitor your financial and health records</strong> closely for unusual activity.</li>
            <li><strong>Limit personal information shared online</strong> to reduce further exposure risks.</li>
            <li><strong>Stay vigilant for phishing attempts</strong> via emails, calls, and texts.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>A Call for National Vigilance</h2>
    <p>The Department of Homeland Security, along with cybersecurity experts, is working tirelessly to investigate and secure compromised systems. This crisis highlights the need for all Americans to take proactive measures to protect their digital identities.</p>

    <h2>Stay Informed</h2>
    <p>For real-time updates and guidance, visit the official response website at <a href="https://www.cybersecurityUSA.gov" target="_blank">www.cybersecurityUSA.gov</a> or call the cybersecurity emergency helpline at <strong>1-800-CYBER24</strong>.</p>

</div>

